The paper deals with the verification of security protocols, specifically with privacy properties. This falls under the category of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a type system for proving equivalence of protocols, which is related to "Logic in Computer Science" (cs.LO) and "Programming Languages" (cs.PL). The implementation and testing of the proposed technique involves software engineering aspects, which could be classified under "Software Engineering" (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of protocols, which could be related to "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DS).
